{{Quote|The Law Enforcement Tools Provision. I can recall all data accessed from this origination point anytime in the last month.|[[Gwad Raatu]]|<ref name="Legacy of the Force: Tempest">''[[Legacy of the Force: Tempest]]''</ref>}}
The '''Law Enforcement Tools Provision''' was a section of the [[Galactic Loyalty Act]] that eliminated the need for quorums to pass anti-terrorist legislation. It also allowed Alliance security personnel to access any private information and data on an individual, including their own [[Datapad/Legends|datapads]] or other private [[Computer/Legends|computers]].

It passed by five votes, itself due to the lessened quorum requirements caused by the withdrawal of the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] [[Senator/Legends|senators]]. Using the Law Enforcement Tools Provision, the [[Galactic Alliance Senate]] passed the [[Suspicious Silence Provision]].

